titlestmt.titleproper:
Guide to the Outpunk Archive
1989-1998
MSS 297
titlestmt.author: Finding aid prepared by Rosemary K. J. Davis, 2011

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using the Archivists' Toolkit 2011-04-27T17:16-0400

did.abstract: Founded by Matt Wobensmith, Outpunk was both a zine, published from 1992-1997, and a queercore record label, releasing music from 1992-1998. This collection contains original masters for almost all of the Outpunk zines, as well as a wide variety of documentation about the bands represented by the Outpunk label, including audio recordings.

bioghist.head: Biographical/Historical note
bioghist.p: In the early 1990's, the queercore movement was small and largely underground. Wobensmith's writing on the subject, along with his subsequent foray into making queercore music more widely available, gave the movement a more public voice.

Inspired by the Riot Grrrl movement, Wobensmith latched on to the burgeoning DIY culture and translated it into an exploration of the styles, trends, and sounds of the queer, hardcore community by publishing seven issues of the Outpunk zine between 1992-1997. Outpunk zines discussed queer culture, punk rock music, sexual politics, the gay skinhead movement, and feminism.
As a record label, Outpunk provided exposure to queer-focused bands including Tribe 8, Pansy Division, the Mukilteo Fairies, Cypher in the Snow, Sta-Prest, and Behead the Prophet No Lord Shall Live.

After ending both the zine and the record label in the late 1990's, Matt Wobensmith continued to stay involved with zine culture. Today he owns and operates Goteblüd, a zine store and archive in San Francisco.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: The Outpunk Archive contains paper files, photography and some media relating to both Outpunk the zine, and Outpunk, the queercore music label. These files include original artwork and flats for Outpunk zines; some administrative records; correspondence between the founder, Matt Wobensmith, and other artists; photographs of artists; copies of Outpunk record releases; and miscellaneous materials that arrived with the collection.
This series contains original flats (master copies) and finished copies of zines created by Matt Wobensmith, as well as some others submitted for distribution by Outpunk.

Subseries B: Other Zines

scopecontent.p: This series contains documentation, photography, invoices, and correspondence pertaining to bands whose work was distributed by or related to the Outpunk label. Bands include Tribe 8, Team Dresch, Pansy Division, God is My Co-Pilot, and Cyryus.

list.item:
Subseries A: Bands and Promo Materials
Subseries B: Miscellaneous Documentation
Subseries C: Miscellaneous Photos

scopecontent.p: This series contains albums released by the Outpunk label. Bands include Tribe 8, Cypher in the Snow, God is My Co-Pilot, Hyperdrive Kittens, Pansy Division, and Sta-Prest.
This series contains oversize photography, posters, and artwork, as well as a collection of band t-shirts and a skateboard.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p:
Published citations should take the following form:
Identification of item, date (if known); collection name; MSS number; box number; folder number; Fales Library and Special Collections, New York University Libraries.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Collection use is subject to all copyright laws. Permission to publish materials must be obtained in writing from the Director of Fales Library and Special Collections. Please contact fales.library@nyu.edu. or call 212 998 2596.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Items have been arranged with the original order kept intact; the only exceptions are oversized and dimensional materials, which are housed in separate containers.
